## Errors & mistakes
- First version was 195 lines (over-engineered). Reverted per "minimize churn".
- ruff PLR6201: `in ("minor","major")` -> `in {"minor","major"}` (set literal).
- bump-my-version refuses to run with a dirty working tree even under
  --dry-run (allow_dirty=false), so dry-running against the live repo while my
  edits were uncommitted failed; verified in clean sandboxes instead.

## Dead ends
- --new-version pinning on every step + a Python plan_versions() helper + a
  pytest self-check file (scripts/test_bump_python_sdk_version.py). It made the
  dry-run preview byte-accurate but tripled the diff. Deleted; native
  bump-my-version computation is correct and needs no Python math, so there is
  no non-trivial logic left to unit-test.

## Hints & warnings
- The part-arg is mandatory: `bump-my-version bump --new-version X ./file`
  errors ("Unknown version component: ./file") because the file positional is
  taken as the version part. Keep `bump <part> <file>`.
- minor/major --dry-run preview: Step 0 shows the real segment target, but the
  drop/tag and next-dev steps preview from the CURRENT version (the pre-step
  isn't applied in dry-run), so they show patch-style numbers. The real run is
  correct because each step sees the prior commit. Documented in the memory note.
- The Action uses native bump (default "Release version: A -> B" commit
  message), consistent with its other commits. The earlier manual 0.53.0 minor
  used "chore(weave): Bump to 0.53.0" (commits 7293299318 + ebaa175f44); same
  version outcomes.
- uv / uvx / gh all live at /opt/homebrew/bin, not on the default shell PATH.
- `ls` is aliased to `eza` in this shell (not installed) — use find/Read.

## Codebase discoveries
- pyproject [tool.bumpversion]: pre_l part values ["dev","final"],
  optional_value "final"; serialize drops the suffix when final. version.py
  VERSION is the source of truth, synced with pyproject current_version on
  every bump. Repo is currently at 0.53.0 (post-minor final state, not -dev0).
- scripts/ has no __init__/conftest and no testpaths in pytest config, so it is
  not collected by the nox shards.

